 \frac{\sin 2x + \sin 4x + \sin 6x}{\cos 2x + \cos 4x + \cos 6x}=? 
\displaystyle\sin2x+\sin4x+\sin6x=\frac{2\sin x(\sin2x+\sin4x+\sin6x)}{2\sin x}=\frac{\cos x-\cos7x}{2\sin x}
\displaystyle\cos C-\cos D=2\sin\frac{C+D}2\sin\frac{D-C}2,
\displaystyle\cos x-\cos7x=2\sin4x\sin3x
\displaystyle\cos2x+\cos4x+\cos6x=\frac{\sin7x-\sin x}{2\sin x}
\displaystyle\sin C-\sin D=2\sin\frac{C-D}2\cos\frac{C+D}2, \sin7x-\sin x=2\sin3x\cos4x
\displaystyle\sin C+\sin D=2\sin\frac{C+D}2\cos\frac{C-D}2
\displaystyle\sin2x+\sin6x
\displaystyle\cos C+\cos D=2\cos\frac{C+D}2\cos\frac{C-D}2
\displaystyle\cos2x+\cos6x
